3 through 2006, to remain available until expended” for “$1,000,000 for fiscal year 1998, $2,000,000 for fiscal year 1999, $4,000,000 for fiscal year 2000, $4,000,000 for fiscal year 2001, and $4,000,000 for fiscal year 2002”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/107/310/s7/a/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 107–310, § 7(a)(1)","children":[],"tail":", made technical amendment to reference in original act which appears in text as reference to "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t33/s467h"},"text":"section 467h of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (a)(2)(A)(i), (ii). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/107/310/s7/b/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 107–310, § 7(b)(1)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “section 467f(e)” for “section 467f(f)”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (a)(2)(C). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/107/310/s7/b/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 107–310, § 7(b)(2)","children":[],"tail":", struck out “needing primary assistance and States needing advanced assistance under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t33/s467f/f"},"text":"section 467f(f) of this title","children":[],"tail":"” before period at end."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsecs. (c) to (e). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/107/310/s7/c"},"text":"Pub. L. 107–310, § 7(c)","children":[],"tail":", added subsecs. (c) to (e) and struck out former subsecs. (c) to (e) which authorized appropriations for fiscal years 1998 through 2002 for dam safety training, research, and staff."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"id6b368801-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"transferOfFunctions","id":"id6b368802-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Transfer of Functions","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"For transfer of all functions, personnel, assets, components, authorities, grant programs, and liabilities of the Federal Emergency Management Agency, including the functions of the Under Secretary for Federal Emergency Management relating thereto, to the Federal Emergency Management Agency, see ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t6/s315/a/1"},"text":"section 315(a)(1) of Title 6","children":[],"tail":", Domestic Security."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"For transfer of functions, personnel, assets, and liabilities of the Federal Emergency Management Agency, including the functions of the Administrator of the Federal Emergency Management Agency relating thereto, to the Secretary of Homeland Security, and for treatment of related references, see former section 313(1) and sections 551(d), 552(d), and 557 of Title 6, Domestic Security, and the Department of Homeland Security Reorganization Plan of ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2002-11-25"},"text":"November 25, 2002","children":[],"tail":", as modified, set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t6/s542"},"text":"section 542 of Title 6","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
